# Running a Single HTTP Check

Based on the verified operation details, here's how to run a single HTTP check:

## Basic Example

```typescript
import { Client } from 'sdk';

const client = new Client({
  baseUrl: 'http://localhost:3000',
});

// Run a simple GET check
const result = await client.request('POST /check/http', {
  "url": "https://www.example.com",
  "method": "GET",
  "regions": ["ams"],
  "runCount": 1
});

console.log(result);
```

## Advanced Example with Custom Headers

```typescript
// Run a POST check with custom headers and body
const advancedResult = await client.request('POST /check/http', {
  "url": "https://api.example.com/health",
  "method": "POST",
  "body": "Hello World",
  "headers": [
    {
      "key": "x-apikey",
      "value": "your-api-key"
    },
    {
      "key": "Content-Type", 
      "value": "application/json"
    }
  ],
  "regions": ["ams", "fra", "lax"],
  "runCount": 3,
  "aggregated": true
});
```

## Configuration Options

- **`url`** (required): The URL to check
- **`method`**: HTTP method - `GET`, `POST`, or `HEAD` (default: `GET`)
- **`body`**: Request body content (optional)
- **`headers`**: Array of key-value header pairs (optional)
- **`regions`**: Array of regions to run the check from (optional)
  - Available regions: `ams`, `arn`, `atl`, `bog`, `bom`, `bos`, `cdg`, `den`, `dfw`, `ewr`, `eze`, `fra`, `gdl`, `gig`, `gru`, `hkg`, `iad`, `jnb`, `lax`, `lhr`, `mad`, `mia`, `nrt`, `ord`, `otp`, `phx`, `qro`, `scl`, `sjc`, `sea`, `sin`, `syd`, `waw`, `yul`, `yyz`
- **`runCount`**: Number of times to run the check (max: 5, default: 1)
- **`aggregated`**: Whether to aggregate results (optional)

This endpoint allows you to quickly test a URL without creating a permanent monitor. Perfect for one-off health checks or testing during development!

